 not new, it has further divided Indonesian Muslims. The introduction of Islamic law would also affect the future of multi-cultural and multi-religious Indonesia. So far, however, the introduction of shari’a nationwide has been opposed by the majority of Indonesian Muslims. This book gives an overview of shari’a from post-Independence in 1945 to the most recent developments in Indonesia at the start of the new millennium.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aIndonesia. 0aIslamic law. 0aPolitical aspects. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Islamic Studies.2bisacsh1 aAzra, Azyumardi, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAzra, Azyumardi, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aCammack, Mark, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFederspiel, Howard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHefner, Robert W., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHooker, M. B., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHosen, Nadirsyah, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLubis, Nur Ahmad Fadhil, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLukito, Ratno, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMawardi, Ahmad Imam, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSalim, Arskal, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSalim, Arskal, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAsian Studies Backlist (2000-2014) eBook Packagez978311064977208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertISEAS Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2015z978311066300608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertISEAS eBook Pa